The Management of Ambrose Alli University (AAU), Ekpoma, has ordered the closure of the University and gave the students 24 hours to move out over what it described as “the roll-over national strike embarked upon by the Academic Staff Union of Universities (ASUU)”. This was contained in a statement signed by Edward U. Aihevba, the Acting Registrar of the University on Monday. According to the statement, “the Management of Ambrose Alli University, Ekpoma, has on behalf of the Senate, approved the temporary suspension of academic activities in the University as a result of the roll-over national strike embarked upon by the Academic Staff Union of Universities (ASUU). “Consequently, all students are directed to vacate the Halls of Residence on or before midnight of Tuesday, March 22, 2022. “They are to return when the University announces the resumption of academic activities. “Administrative activities in the University will, however, continue without any interruption. “This is for the Information and guidance of all students, staff and the University community”, the statement further stated.